Commit Description: Now instead of reading version from the lock files and needing several lockfile parsers to work, the CLI can read version from each package's package.json after resolving the file path using require.resolve, as suggested by @andreialecu

Reading from the appropriate lock files instead of the package.json means having a better idea of what packages are installed. With the package.json, there's a chance to miss the actual installed version due to using a range like ^7.0.0 whereas with the lock file, the version is printed to what the package manager resolved. To make this more easily achievable, I refactored the info.action.ts file to be more class based so I could reuse the package manager instead of having to re-find it each time. re: #896
